==Description==

'''Level 622''', Mountain Village, is a large village on a mountaintop. Weather that is neither hot nor cold but ever so light, the level appears to be forever summer. Medieval in character in its buildings are discernible, projecting an ageless, serene setting.

This phase has several effects that alter an individual's perception of the world around them. They vary from dizziness, and fatigue, to visual hallucinations—such as perceiving things or creatures that do not exist. What makes these effects so unusual is the fact that, once the effects subside, the body experiences a surge of energy, with a release of oxytocin, serotonin, dopamine, and endorphins. This biochemical process gives way to a tremendous sense of calm and emotional stability in the subject.

Furthermore, the process has been observed to significantly reduce the risks of contracting disorders such as [[Phenomenon 35]] or [[Phenomenon 52]].

==The Grand Plaza==

It is the largest area of the entire village: a flat, open space with a church at the center, a fountain also at the center, and several small shops surrounding it. These shops sell food, dolls, and various other items. Some of these shops are operated by [[A.A.E.G.|Λ.λ.∈.G]].

The plaza itself is quite sparsely decorated, as there is nothing of particular interest beyond the shops themselves. That being said, some shops contain rather strange items, such as plushies of entities and other curious objects, giving the impression that these establishments function like souvenir shops.

== The Village Houses ==

The village houses tend to be on narrow streets, where the effect of the level is most felt. It's like the walls themselves are pulling in the strange energy that clings to the air, so the air is heavier and denser. The structures themselves, however, faded and venerable, seem a natural continuation of the land itself, standing mute as though time had never reached them, and the gentle warp of the level insinuates itself into each nook and cranny unobserved by those who live in them.

== The Mountains ==

The hills surround the village completely, forming a natural wall that cuts off the world from it. The village lies between their slopes, and no human has ever crossed beyond on an expedition. While they look high and close, they also look inaccessible, as if there is something keeping human beings away from crossing. Despite their ubiquity, the hills do not demand adventure, and the village just stays in their shadow without seeking anything beyond the confines.

==Bases, Colonies and Outposts==

The only base within the level is located in the village itself, Base A or simply the Main Base of [[A.A.E.G.]]. The greatest and most well-known base in the level, the Main Base has complete dominance over everything that takes place there. Despite such dominance, however, the base remains open to anyone who might want to enter it. Although the base has collapsed in the past, such as in '''(Protocol: Found Exit)''', it recovered and is now a place where any traveller would get shelter. Symptoms that afflict visitors occur every 5 hours accompanied by very light dizziness, but the base remains a relatively safe place nonetheless.

==Entrances and Exits==

=Entrances=

*At [[level 5]] if you find a door that has a drawing of an A and you open it you will arrive here

*If you enter a medieval style house at [[level 9]] it will take you here

=Exits=

*Leave the town through its main entrance, it will take you to [[level 778]]


